1
00:00:22,464 --> 00:00:26,432
♪Should we forget yesterday's sorrows♪

2
00:00:26,432 --> 00:00:29,728
♪And the dazed confusion♪

3
00:00:30,976 --> 00:00:33,681
♪Should we let go of♪

4
00:00:33,681 --> 00:00:35,904
♪The stubborn madness♪

5
00:00:35,904 --> 00:00:39,072
♪And naive recklessness now♪

6
00:00:40,192 --> 00:00:43,840
♪Those years, those faces♪

7
00:00:44,992 --> 00:00:48,763
♪Those old scars we can't erase♪

8
00:00:49,824 --> 00:00:52,460
♪Tears streaming, facing the light♪

9
00:00:53,152 --> 00:00:57,594
♪Piercing the sorrow within♪

10
00:01:08,716 --> 00:01:12,736
♪The road ahead's long,
stumbling all the way♪

11
00:01:13,536 --> 00:01:18,076
♪The wounds we've borne
are medals hidden within♪

12
00:01:18,336 --> 00:01:22,391
♪Standing alone on an open plain♪

13
00:01:23,168 --> 00:01:26,851
♪We gaze at the stars♪

14
00:01:31,228 --> 00:01:34,816
=The Dream Maker=

15
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:38,005
=Episode 19=

16
00:01:54,706 --> 00:01:55,306
Yan?

17
00:01:56,306 --> 00:01:56,806
Yan.

18
00:01:57,467 --> 00:01:58,946
Why are you back? What are you doing?

19
00:02:00,827 --> 00:02:01,327
I'll do it.

20
00:02:04,907 --> 00:02:05,627
Let's go quickly.

21
00:02:05,946 --> 00:02:08,387
The typhoon is coming.
It's too dangerous. Let's go.

22
00:02:08,746 --> 00:02:09,387
Mr. Lin,

23
00:02:09,667 --> 00:02:11,586
I know it's wrong for me
to come back suddenly.

24
00:02:12,026 --> 00:02:13,592
Leave me alone. Just go.

25
00:02:16,760 --> 00:02:17,746
Are you crazy?

26
00:02:18,026 --> 00:02:19,447
People matter more. Let's go.

27
00:02:20,146 --> 00:02:21,026
Mr. Lin!

28
00:02:21,746 --> 00:02:22,987
Leave me alone.

29
00:02:23,267 --> 00:02:24,626
I earned this cement

30
00:02:24,626 --> 00:02:26,267
by selling countless bowls of wontons.

31
00:02:26,306 --> 00:02:28,186
I can't just watch it
get ruined by water.

32
00:02:28,267 --> 00:02:29,107
You should go.

33
00:02:32,146 --> 00:02:33,186
Fine. Go in. I'll do it.

34
00:02:41,787 --> 00:02:42,626
Leave it to me.

35
00:02:51,227 --> 00:02:51,727
Hurry up.

36
00:02:52,754 --> 00:02:54,616
(Yuehai People's Hospital)

37
00:02:55,026 --> 00:02:56,787
Ms. Li, it's too late.

38
00:02:57,146 --> 00:02:58,306
Let's get into the hospital.

39
00:02:58,746 --> 00:02:59,246
Let's go.

40
00:03:01,067 --> 00:03:01,667
Be careful.

41
00:03:03,146 --> 00:03:03,646
Come on.

42
00:03:05,394 --> 00:03:11,218
(Yuehai People's Hospital)

43
00:03:14,227 --> 00:03:15,787
I remember it was here.

44
00:03:17,466 --> 00:03:18,586
Where is it, Mr. Zheng?

45
00:03:22,827 --> 00:03:24,746
See? I told you the wind was coming.

46
00:03:27,347 --> 00:03:28,267
And it's not small.

47
00:03:28,586 --> 00:03:30,547
Mr. Zheng, thank you.

48
00:03:31,787 --> 00:03:32,426
What for?

49
00:03:33,466 --> 00:03:34,667
Thank you for saving my life.

50
00:03:35,746 --> 00:03:37,746
It's nothing. Just life experience.

51
00:03:53,202 --> 00:03:54,194
(Promoting the Five Do's,
Four Upliftings, and Three Loves)

52
00:04:50,946 --> 00:04:52,506
It should be right here.

53
00:04:53,626 --> 00:04:54,826
What are you looking for?

54
00:04:54,946 --> 00:04:57,066
Ms. Li, stand right here.
And wait for me.

55
00:04:58,667 --> 00:04:59,426
Be careful.

56
00:05:00,467 --> 00:05:03,266
I... I remember the distribution box
should be here.

57
00:05:06,907 --> 00:05:07,407
Here it is.

58
00:05:15,306 --> 00:05:15,907
What's wrong?

59
00:05:17,066 --> 00:05:18,066
This door won't open.

60
00:05:18,147 --> 00:05:19,866
Give me a second. Don't move yet.

61
00:05:29,227 --> 00:05:30,386
Move aside.

62
00:05:34,987 --> 00:05:35,487
Oh no.

63
00:05:35,787 --> 00:05:37,946
Could this door
be jammed from the outside?

64
00:05:38,186 --> 00:05:39,066
What do we do now?

65
00:05:39,587 --> 00:05:41,547
Have we really reached the end
of our lives?

66
00:05:44,107 --> 00:05:44,826
That can't be.

67
00:05:48,707 --> 00:05:49,506
We are in...

68
00:05:52,946 --> 00:05:53,787
The morgue?

69
00:05:54,467 --> 00:05:56,027
Is this really fate's arrangement?

70
00:05:56,626 --> 00:05:59,347
Mr. Zheng, don't jinx us.

71
00:06:02,266 --> 00:06:03,707
Knock on wood. Knock on wood.

72
00:06:04,426 --> 00:06:07,386
My mouth isn't usually this prophetic.
Seriously.

73
00:06:10,147 --> 00:06:12,186
Ms. Li, are you scared?

74
00:06:14,066 --> 00:06:14,987
Scared?

75
00:06:15,707 --> 00:06:17,946
(Emergency)
I'm an atheist. I'm not scared at all.

76
00:06:19,147 --> 00:06:20,147
I just think

77
00:06:20,306 --> 00:06:21,186
with strong winds,

78
00:06:21,587 --> 00:06:24,547
it's absurd that we're trapped here.

79
00:06:24,946 --> 00:06:27,027
This Category 12 typhoon
will last for a while.

80
00:06:27,306 --> 00:06:28,306
It may last a day or two.

81
00:06:29,667 --> 00:06:31,386
I doubt anyone will rescue us now.

82
00:06:31,866 --> 00:06:33,987
Don't worry about outside.

83
00:06:34,266 --> 00:06:36,107
Everyone who needed to evacuate
has done so.

84
00:06:36,386 --> 00:06:38,987
Xie and Tan must've arranged shelter
for all the residents.

85
00:06:43,946 --> 00:06:45,506
This thing is precious.

86
00:06:46,186 --> 00:06:47,987
Mr. Lin made this himself.

87
00:06:48,547 --> 00:06:50,506
What a waste if it gets waterlogged.

88
00:06:51,707 --> 00:06:53,667
Mr. Zheng, you were looking
for this all along?

89
00:06:58,587 --> 00:07:01,547
Ms. Li, well, let's rest.

90
00:07:02,587 --> 00:07:03,587
Anyway, we're stuck here.

91
00:07:03,866 --> 00:07:05,506
Rest properly now.

92
00:07:06,107 --> 00:07:07,266
We're here. Let's accept it.

93
00:07:08,066 --> 00:07:09,626
Lie down and relax.

94
00:07:10,027 --> 00:07:11,186
Let's wait the typhoon out.

95
00:07:12,787 --> 00:07:14,907
Honestly, it's quite comfortable here.

96
00:07:17,626 --> 00:07:18,266
Mr. Zheng,

97
00:07:19,147 --> 00:07:22,027
why do you care so much
about this sign and the hospital?

98
00:07:23,707 --> 00:07:24,907
Because of my wife.

99
00:07:26,467 --> 00:07:30,707
Many years ago,
Yuehai was just marshland.

100
00:07:31,866 --> 00:07:34,386
My wife taught
at a village school nearby then.

101
00:07:35,426 --> 00:07:37,907
One night, she got sudden stomach pains.

102
00:07:38,866 --> 00:07:40,626
So I took her to the clinic.

103
00:07:41,907 --> 00:07:43,946
But those young medics
didn't know anything.

104
00:07:44,787 --> 00:07:46,306
They suggested the county hospital.

105
00:07:47,467 --> 00:07:50,426
So I rushed her to the county hospital.

106
00:07:51,707 --> 00:07:53,066
But before we got there,

107
00:07:54,227 --> 00:07:55,186
she was gone.

108
00:08:00,626 --> 00:08:02,227
It wasn't even a serious illness.

109
00:08:03,587 --> 00:08:04,907
Just acute appendicitis.

110
00:08:05,987 --> 00:08:08,907
Any surgeon
could've performed the surgery.

111
00:08:10,587 --> 00:08:12,186
I... I'm sorry.

112
00:08:12,707 --> 00:08:13,207
It's fine.

113
00:08:15,386 --> 00:08:16,587
So,

114
00:08:18,266 --> 00:08:21,426
after coming to Yuehai,
I vowed to build a hospital.

115
00:08:23,107 --> 00:08:24,347
A proper hospital.

116
00:08:26,826 --> 00:08:29,186
It can cure illnesses
and perform surgeries.

117
00:08:30,587 --> 00:08:31,707
And it needs

118
00:08:32,546 --> 00:08:33,906
to have an emergency sign

119
00:08:34,987 --> 00:08:38,786
hung high and bright.

120
00:08:40,427 --> 00:08:43,067
So people who need it
can spot it from afar

121
00:08:43,947 --> 00:08:47,666
in critical moments.

122
00:08:49,666 --> 00:08:50,746
In this life,

123
00:08:51,906 --> 00:08:53,067
you can overcome anything.

124
00:08:54,666 --> 00:08:55,227
Really.

125
00:09:15,987 --> 00:09:16,707
Coming through.

126
00:09:35,227 --> 00:09:36,026
Thanks, Xiaoyu.

127
00:09:37,386 --> 00:09:38,626
I should be thanking you.

128
00:09:39,026 --> 00:09:40,408
Let me know if you need anything.

129
00:09:40,987 --> 00:09:41,487
Okay.

130
00:09:43,347 --> 00:09:44,666
Drink up. Don't catch a cold.

131
00:09:48,266 --> 00:09:48,766
Here.

132
00:09:49,107 --> 00:09:50,786
Here, Xiaohai, your carrying fee.

133
00:09:51,427 --> 00:09:54,467
Ms. Gao, I didn't help carry anything.
I can't take this money.

134
00:09:54,626 --> 00:09:56,026
But you carried me.

135
00:09:57,067 --> 00:09:59,347
Just showing up in this weather
is helping enough.

136
00:10:00,107 --> 00:10:01,707
Consider it an advance.

137
00:10:01,906 --> 00:10:04,026
Help me carry things
after the typhoon, okay?

138
00:10:04,187 --> 00:10:04,746
Well...

139
00:10:04,786 --> 00:10:05,286
Take it.

140
00:10:06,427 --> 00:10:06,927
Alright.

141
00:10:07,146 --> 00:10:09,187
All of you, drink some
to prevent catching a chill.

142
00:10:09,347 --> 00:10:10,107
Thank you all.

143
00:10:10,546 --> 00:10:12,266
Xiaoyu, add some more water.

144
00:10:13,786 --> 00:10:14,467
Mr. Zheng.

145
00:10:17,587 --> 00:10:18,187
Mr. Zheng.

146
00:10:21,307 --> 00:10:23,347
How... how did I fall asleep?

147
00:10:24,107 --> 00:10:26,257
This bed really is different, isn't it?

148
00:10:26,456 --> 00:10:28,187
Lying here brings me complete peace.

149
00:10:28,266 --> 00:10:29,307
It just flew by.

150
00:10:31,626 --> 00:10:33,987
I mean, I slept right through.

151
00:10:35,146 --> 00:10:35,646
Okay.

152
00:10:41,587 --> 00:10:43,786
You're not bad. Quite nimble.

153
00:10:44,506 --> 00:10:45,107
Not bad.

154
00:10:55,067 --> 00:10:55,746
Ms. Li.

155
00:10:57,026 --> 00:10:58,227
Can I ask you a question?

156
00:11:01,386 --> 00:11:04,347
Do you regret coming to Yuehai?

157
00:11:07,746 --> 00:11:08,786
Why would you ask that?

158
00:11:10,266 --> 00:11:11,467
Look,

159
00:11:12,227 --> 00:11:14,347
before the county decided

160
00:11:15,386 --> 00:11:16,587
to build Yuehai into a city,

161
00:11:16,866 --> 00:11:18,587
it was a place no one would want.

162
00:11:18,987 --> 00:11:20,067
You're an educated person,

163
00:11:20,467 --> 00:11:21,827
respectable and nice-looking.

164
00:11:22,266 --> 00:11:24,746
Why volunteer to come here and suffer?

165
00:11:25,987 --> 00:11:28,026
You're right. I deeply regret it.

166
00:11:29,067 --> 00:11:29,567
Right?

167
00:11:30,546 --> 00:11:32,947
When I first came to Yuehai,
I was full of passion.

168
00:11:33,746 --> 00:11:36,987
But I didn't expect
to face so many difficulties at work.

169
00:11:38,067 --> 00:11:40,906
Many things were new to me.
I was handling them for the first time.

170
00:11:41,626 --> 00:11:43,786
But I had to grit my teeth
and do them anyway.

171
00:11:45,427 --> 00:11:48,626
All this back and forth
left me no time to visit my parents.

172
00:11:49,266 --> 00:11:50,347
Most importantly,

173
00:11:53,347 --> 00:11:55,266
I couldn't properly talk with my friend.

174
00:12:04,467 --> 00:12:05,746
Friend, well...

175
00:12:06,307 --> 00:12:09,087
People come and go.
That's perfectly normal, right?

176
00:12:09,266 --> 00:12:11,866
You're still young, lacking experience.

177
00:12:12,427 --> 00:12:13,107
Look at me.

178
00:12:13,347 --> 00:12:14,936
I loved drinking and fighting as a kid.

179
00:12:15,427 --> 00:12:16,546
Then I met my wife.

180
00:12:16,906 --> 00:12:19,067
I promised her
I'd quit drinking and fighting.

181
00:12:19,626 --> 00:12:22,746
Overnight, all my friends vanished.

182
00:12:25,187 --> 00:12:28,827
I remember reading an essay in school.

183
00:12:29,427 --> 00:12:30,506
It left a deep impression.

184
00:12:33,707 --> 00:12:37,026
Friends are merely fellow travelers

185
00:12:37,386 --> 00:12:38,827
on life's lonely journey.

186
00:12:40,107 --> 00:12:41,266
Once a certain part is done,

187
00:12:41,906 --> 00:12:44,227
it's their freedom to turn.

188
00:12:44,746 --> 00:12:46,347
But while walking together,

189
00:12:47,386 --> 00:12:49,026
if you fall, they help you up.

190
00:12:49,746 --> 00:12:52,067
If wild beasts attack,
you resist together.

191
00:12:52,906 --> 00:12:54,026
That's only natural.

192
00:12:54,947 --> 00:12:57,427
Once paths diverge,
you may care for each other,

193
00:12:58,107 --> 00:13:00,307
but you can no longer lend aid.

194
00:13:00,987 --> 00:13:01,987
But then,

195
00:13:02,467 --> 00:13:05,987
new fellow travelers may come along.

196
00:13:09,827 --> 00:13:10,386
Mr. Zheng,

197
00:13:11,666 --> 00:13:13,427
how do you know an essay
like that by heart?

198
00:13:14,067 --> 00:13:14,866
So,

199
00:13:15,146 --> 00:13:17,506
I believe life's journey is long.

200
00:13:17,906 --> 00:13:20,187
You make friends
for each chapter of life.

201
00:13:20,626 --> 00:13:23,266
If interests align,
you walk together longer, right?

202
00:13:23,546 --> 00:13:25,307
If interests differ, just drop it.

203
00:13:25,947 --> 00:13:26,786
Part ways amicably.

204
00:13:27,067 --> 00:13:29,807
Anyone can live without anyone else
in this world, right?

205
00:13:30,307 --> 00:13:31,107
Therefore,

206
00:13:31,506 --> 00:13:34,227
friends are merely fellow travelers

207
00:13:34,506 --> 00:13:36,187
on life's lonely journey.

208
00:13:38,994 --> 00:13:40,408
(Tea)

209
00:14:25,386 --> 00:14:28,026
Mr. Lin, are you holding up?

210
00:14:28,947 --> 00:14:29,546
Don't worry.

211
00:14:32,427 --> 00:14:35,067
If the sky falls,
I'll hold it up for you.

212
00:14:38,987 --> 00:14:40,587
Come on. There's news.

213
00:14:47,467 --> 00:14:48,146
On Binhai Road,

214
00:14:48,227 --> 00:14:49,687
I... I just...

215
00:14:50,227 --> 00:14:52,906
I often worked over ten hours
at a stretch.

216
00:14:54,026 --> 00:14:56,126
Back when we built Binhai Road, I...

217
00:14:58,107 --> 00:14:59,366
I'm sorry, I...

218
00:15:26,107 --> 00:15:27,707
Yan... Yan.

219
00:15:28,227 --> 00:15:28,827
What?

220
00:15:32,746 --> 00:15:33,587
Listen, Yan.

221
00:15:36,187 --> 00:15:37,146
A beauty I beheld,

222
00:15:38,107 --> 00:15:38,827
unforgettable.

223
00:15:38,898 --> 00:15:41,646
♪The white doves across the lake♪

224
00:15:44,347 --> 00:15:46,187
Even though I've crossed bridges
in many places

225
00:15:49,626 --> 00:15:51,107
and seen clouds in many places...

226
00:15:51,386 --> 00:15:52,827
Mr. Lin finally said it?

227
00:15:56,107 --> 00:15:57,307
Only your eyes

228
00:15:58,906 --> 00:16:00,467
have ever held a cloudless sky.

229
00:16:04,746 --> 00:16:05,587
Why are you laughing?

230
00:16:06,866 --> 00:16:07,366
Listen.

231
00:16:09,266 --> 00:16:10,266
You look at me

232
00:16:11,227 --> 00:16:12,026
and at the clouds.

233
00:16:12,146 --> 00:16:13,107
Isn't this Lin?

234
00:16:17,107 --> 00:16:19,187
When you look at me, it feels distant.

235
00:16:19,827 --> 00:16:21,266
No. When you look at me, it's far.

236
00:16:21,506 --> 00:16:22,866
But the clouds feel close.

237
00:16:25,347 --> 00:16:25,947
What was that?

238
00:16:26,506 --> 00:16:27,906
How could he forget? Seriously.

239
00:16:29,546 --> 00:16:30,666
He's quite good at this.

240
00:16:30,746 --> 00:16:31,786
Not good with words?

241
00:16:32,266 --> 00:16:33,546
The wind knocked sense into him.

242
00:16:40,024 --> 00:16:43,909
♪You're the gentle passage of a book♪

243
00:16:44,067 --> 00:16:44,987
Mr. Lin,

244
00:16:47,746 --> 00:16:52,906
you're the most reliable
and responsible man I've ever met.

245
00:16:57,587 --> 00:16:58,266
It worked.

246
00:17:01,067 --> 00:17:01,720
Take it easy.

247
00:17:08,227 --> 00:17:10,227
But Mr. Lin,

248
00:17:11,907 --> 00:17:14,227
you're a cadre, a mayor.

249
00:17:15,026 --> 00:17:16,667
While I'm just a wonton seller,

250
00:17:17,387 --> 00:17:18,506
and I have a child.

251
00:17:20,627 --> 00:17:21,467
Do you mind?

252
00:17:21,987 --> 00:17:22,826
I don't mind.

253
00:17:24,266 --> 00:17:26,506
I'll even give you my monthly salary.

254
00:17:35,410 --> 00:17:38,674
♪You're but a fleeting spark♪

255
00:17:39,576 --> 00:17:42,721
♪The white doves across the lake♪

256
00:17:46,867 --> 00:17:47,707
Look at him.

257
00:17:48,106 --> 00:17:50,026
Don't you know where my money went?

258
00:17:52,907 --> 00:17:54,907
What about my machine?

259
00:17:57,066 --> 00:17:58,907
Well, Lin is quite down-to-earth.

260
00:18:00,066 --> 00:18:01,266
Remind him to turn it off.

261
00:18:03,826 --> 00:18:04,346
Mr...

262
00:18:04,907 --> 00:18:05,546
Mr. Lin.

263
00:18:07,427 --> 00:18:09,707
This is Li Qiuping. Please respond.

264
00:18:14,346 --> 00:18:15,227
Why no sound?

265
00:18:16,506 --> 00:18:18,746
No. Is it completely out of battery?

266
00:18:18,987 --> 00:18:20,387
No way, at this critical moment?

267
00:18:21,127 --> 00:18:22,707
I... I think I have no signal either.

268
00:18:28,907 --> 00:18:29,407
Oh no.

269
00:18:30,786 --> 00:18:32,147
Why is water flooding in?

270
00:18:40,786 --> 00:18:42,667
It's fine, Ms. Li. Don't worry too much.

271
00:18:43,227 --> 00:18:45,387
Based on my experience,
the water won't rise too fast.

272
00:18:45,947 --> 00:18:48,066
We won't be in danger anytime soon.
Just relax.

273
00:18:57,202 --> 00:18:59,186
(Uphold the Four Cardinal Principles,
Persevere with Reform and Opening-up)

274
00:19:02,738 --> 00:19:04,152
(Roads Open All Trades,
City Construction Thrives)

